<subSubSection id="C37588C1FFDCC953EFD3F9F8FD6BC968" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BD0DB4AFFDCC953EFD3F9F8FD6BC968" blockId="1.[174,1233,1628,1847]" lastBlockId="2.[166,1225,175,298]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDCC950EE07F9F8FD9CCE34" authority="Rafinesque, 1820" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1820" box="[311,604,1628,1654]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDCC950EE07F9F8FE4ACE34" box="[311,394,1628,1654]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Rutilus</emphasis>
Rafinesque, 1820
</taxonomicName>
includes 17 recent species (FishBase, 2014), three of which are found in the water bodies of 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDCC950ED5FF9D8FD0FCED4" box="[623,719,1660,1686]" name="Ukraine" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDCC950EC37F9D8FCB0CED4" box="[775,880,1660,1686]" name="Moldova" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Moldova</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDCC950EC4EF9D8FBF9CED5" author="Movchan, Yu. V." box="[894,1081,1660,1687]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" refId="ref4514" refString="Movchan, Yu. V. Fishes of Ukraine. - Kyiv, 2011. - 444 p. - Ukrainian: Мovcaн Ю. V. Рibi Ukрayнi." type="book" year="2011">Movchan, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). The earliest members of the genus are known from the Oligocene of Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDCC950EC83F938FB56CEF5" author="Sytchevskaya, Y. K." box="[947,1174,1692,1719]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" refId="ref4915" refString="Sytchevskaya, Y. K. Freshwater Neogene Ichthyofauna of Mongolia // Trudy Sovmestnoy Sovetsko-Mongolskoy Paleontologicheskoy Ekspeditsii. - Moscow: Nauka, 1989. - N 39. - 144 p. - Russian: Сыcivсkai I. K. Pрiснovodнai iktioфauнa нiogiнa Мoнgoлii." type="book" year="1989">Sytchevskaya, 1989</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDCC950EF9EF918FF30CE94" box="[174,240,1724,1750]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDCC950EFCDF918FDD9CE95" author="Cabrera, L. &amp; Gaudant, J." box="[253,537,1724,1751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" pagination="219 - 226" refId="ref4137" refString="Cabrera, L., Gaudant, J. Los Cyprinidos (Pisces) del sistema lacustre Oligocenico-Miocenico de los Monegros (sector SE de la Cuenca del Ebro, provincias de Lleida, Torrangona, Huesca y Zaragoza) // Acta geologica Hispanica. - 1985. - 20, is. 3 - 4. - P. 219 - 226." type="book chapter" year="1985">Cabrera, Gaudant, 1985</bibRefCitation>
). According to the molecular data, these fishes colonized the Europe near 35 mya (Ketmaier et al., 2008). Several Roach species were described from the Miocene and Pliocene strata of Europe and Asia: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDCC950EDDFF958FBB2CF55" authority="(Gaudant, 1984)" baseAuthorityName="Gaudant" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[751,1138,1788,1815]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachecri">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDCC950EDDFF958FC69CF54" box="[751,937,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Rutilus pachecri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDCC950EC88F958FBA9CF55" author="Gaudant, J." box="[952,1129,1788,1815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" pagination="463 - 472" refId="ref4335" refString="Gaudant, J. Sur les poisons fossils (Teleosteens, Cyprinidae) des gypses Turoliens du Fosse de Teruel: essai d'approche paleoecologique // Estudios Geologicos. Bulletin de l'Academie Serbe des Sciences et des Arts. - 1984. - 40. - P. 463 - 472." type="book chapter" year="1984">Gaudant, 1984</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDCC950EB4DF958FD90CF75" authority="(Sytchevskaya, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Sytchevskaya" baseAuthorityYear="1989" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tungurukensis">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDCC950EB4DF958FE91CF74" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Rutilus tungurukensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDCC950EE50F8B8FD88CF75" author="Sytchevskaya, Y. K." box="[352,584,1820,1847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" refId="ref4915" refString="Sytchevskaya, Y. K. Freshwater Neogene Ichthyofauna of Mongolia // Trudy Sovmestnoy Sovetsko-Mongolskoy Paleontologicheskoy Ekspeditsii. - Moscow: Nauka, 1989. - N 39. - 144 p. - Russian: Сыcivсkai I. K. Pрiснovodнai iktioфauнa нiogiнa Мoнgoлii." type="book" year="1989">Sytchevskaya, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDCC950ED6CF8B8FC23CF75" authority="(Bogachev, 1938)" baseAuthorityName="Bogachev" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[604,995,1820,1847]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oswaldi">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDCC950ED6CF8B8FCCECF74" box="[604,782,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="412">Rutilus oswaldi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDCC950EC2DF8B8FC1BCF75" author="Bogachev, V. V." box="[797,987,1820,1847]" pageId="1" pageNumber="412" refId="ref3946" refString="Bogachev, V. V. Fauna from the Pliocene diatomit sediments of Transkaukasia // Trudy Azerb. filii Akademii Nauk SSSR. - 1938. - 9, N 39. - P. 61 - 95. - Russian: Bogaciv V. V. Фauнa diatoмitovыk pлiotiнovыk otлoziнiй v Zakavkazьi." type="book" year="1938">Bogachev, 1938</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and also numerous remnants of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDFC953EE0EFF0BFDC8C88B" authority="cf. rutilus" box="[318,520,175,201]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rutilus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953EE0EFF0BFE51C88B" box="[318,401,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Rutilus</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953EE8CFF0BFDC8C88B" box="[444,520,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">rutilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDFC953ED27FF0BFD0AC88B" baseAuthorityName="Nordmann" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[535,714,175,201]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frisii">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953ED27FF0BFDAAC88B" box="[535,618,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Rutilus</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953EDA5FF0BFD0AC88B" box="[661,714,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">frisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDFC953EDE8FF0BFC94C888" box="[728,852,175,202]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953EDE8FF0BFCEBC88B" box="[728,811,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Rutilus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFEA6BBFFDFC953EC54FF0BFBF3C888" author="Bohme, M. &amp; Ilg, A." box="[868,1075,175,202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" refId="ref4094" refString="Bohme, M., Ilg, A. Database of Vertebrates: fossil Fishes, Amphibians, Reptiles and Birds (fosFARbase) localities and taxa from the Triassic to the Neogene. - 2003. - www. wahre-staerke. com" type="book" year="2003">Böhme, Ilg, 2003</bibRefCitation>
). It is safe to say, that five species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDFC953EEEBFF6BFDEEC8AB" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1820" box="[475,558,207,233]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953EEEBFF6BFDEEC8AB" box="[475,558,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Rutilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus have been identified in the Late Miocene and Early Pliocene of 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDFC953EE1FFF4BFE4FC94B" box="[303,399,239,265]" name="Ukraine" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3789BDAFFDFC953EEF9FF4BFDF6C94B" box="[457,566,239,265]" name="Moldova" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Moldova</collectingCountry>
. Here we describe a new fossil Roach, which seems to be close to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6FA0C9FFDFC953EE01FEABFD67C968" authority="(Nordmann, 1840)" baseAuthorityName="Nordmann" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[305,679,271,298]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Rutilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="413" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="frisii">
<emphasis id="B91B0758FFDFC953EE01FEABFE00C96B" box="[305,448,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="413">Rutilus frisii</emphasis>
(Nordmann, 1840)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
